laboratory_examinations.findings: Cystic lesion on the umbilical cord at the fetal end, measuring 3.6 * 1.9 cm.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased in size to 4.3 * 5.7 cm at 34 weeks; further increase in size to 5.5 * 6.0 cm at 35 weeks.

Extensive edema and myxomatous degeneration forming pseudocysts containing mucoid fluid; normal-appearing vessels (2 arteries and 1 vein).
